    <!-- 9. FAQs -->
    <section id="faqs" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-geo-800/60 bg-geo-900/30 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-white mb-3">What is answer engine optimisation?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Answer engine optimisation (AEO) is the practice of structuring website content so that answer engines — including Google's featured snippets, AI Overviews, voice assistants, and AI chatbots — can extract and surface it as a direct response to user queries.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-geo-800/60 bg-geo-900/30 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-white mb-3">How is AEO different from SEO?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Traditional SEO optimises for ranking positions in a list of blue links. AEO optimises for selection as a direct answer. SEO targets click-through from search results pages; AEO targets zero-click visibility where the answer engine presents your content directly to the user.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-geo-800/60 bg-geo-900/30 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-white mb-3">Is AEO part of GEO?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Yes. AEO is a subset of <a href="/generative-engine-optimisation/" class="text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-300 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 transition">Generative Engine Optimisation (GEO)</a>. AEO focuses specifically on answer-box and direct-answer interfaces, while GEO encompasses the broader discipline of optimising for all AI-driven search surfaces, including LLM citations, conversational AI, and generative search experiences.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-geo-800/60 bg-geo-900/30 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-white mb-3">What types of content perform best for AEO?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Content that performs best for AEO follows a clear question-answer structure, uses concise definitions (40-60 words), includes structured data markup like FAQ schema, presents information in lists or tables, and establishes entity clarity through consistent terminology and authoritative sourcing.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-geo-800/60 bg-geo-900/30 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-white mb-3">Do I still need traditional SEO if I do AEO?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Yes. AEO builds on top of strong technical and on-page SEO foundations. Without proper indexing, crawlability, site speed, and topical authority, answer engines are unlikely to select your content. AEO is an additional layer of optimisation, not a replacement for SEO.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

